text: Jamnia may refer to: * Council of Jamnia, a hypothetical Jewish council in the 1st century CE * Jamnia Jagir, a former estate in the Bhopawar Agency of British India * Jamnith (Jamnia), a ruin in Upper Galilee * Yibna, a former village known in Roman sources as Jamnia ** Yavne, a city in the Central District of Israel that occupies the site of the village
title: Jamnia
